1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:26,714 --> 00:00:28,675
-Huh?
-The doors are closing.

3
00:00:32,929 --> 00:00:34,931
YOO SE-AH

4
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:46,317
A transfer student?

5
00:00:46,401 --> 00:00:48,278
Must be a bully.

6
00:00:48,778 --> 00:00:51,656
No, my mom told me about her.

7
00:00:51,739 --> 00:00:54,325
Her parents took their own lives,
so she's on her own.

8
00:00:54,409 --> 00:00:55,577
-Really?
-Really?

9
00:00:55,660 --> 00:00:56,744
That's insane.

10
00:00:57,245 --> 00:00:58,288
What? That's creepy.

11
00:00:58,371 --> 00:01:00,123
Maybe she's got stuff going on too.

12
00:01:00,206 --> 00:01:02,667
There's even a rumor
she killed her parents.

13
00:01:03,585 --> 00:01:05,170
A three-time national champion

14
00:01:05,253 --> 00:01:07,922
and a next-generation Olympic prospect,
Yoo Se-ah.

15
00:01:08,006 --> 00:01:09,883
-Be quiet.
-I'm on the track team too.

16
00:01:09,966 --> 00:01:11,885
-I also do the long jump.
-I said be quiet.

17
00:01:11,968 --> 00:01:13,636
-Hey, she said be quiet!
-Ouch.

18
00:01:14,470 --> 00:01:17,390
Come on, these are a track athlete's legs.

19
00:01:18,892 --> 00:01:20,310
They're basically still

20
00:01:21,895 --> 00:01:25,148
elementary students up here,
so they're inconsiderate.

21
00:01:26,482 --> 00:01:29,402
If anyone bothers you again,
just let me know.

22
00:01:30,778 --> 00:01:34,949
If you need to copy someone's homework,
ask him, not me.

23
00:01:35,033 --> 00:01:37,285
You should do your own homework.

24
00:01:42,832 --> 00:01:44,584
I'm Kang Ha-joon.

25
00:01:45,084 --> 00:01:48,129
Well, since you're new here,
I'll help you out.

26
00:01:48,213 --> 00:01:50,715
I'll help you out with the track team.

27
00:01:51,216 --> 00:01:52,050
Just trust me.

28
00:01:52,675 --> 00:01:53,509
Skul!

29
00:01:54,302 --> 00:01:55,345
Legendary.

30
00:01:55,428 --> 00:01:56,471
The legendary skeleton

31
00:01:56,554 --> 00:01:59,599
who never left the Demon King's side
to the very end!

32
00:02:01,809 --> 00:02:03,770
He's my minion, but you can have him.

33
00:02:06,856 --> 00:02:10,944
He and I will protect you
from all evil schemes.

34
00:02:35,593 --> 00:02:37,804
Hyeong-wook, put the knife down. Okay?

35
00:02:37,887 --> 00:02:38,763
Please calm down.

36
00:02:50,275 --> 00:02:51,609
No!

37
00:02:52,777 --> 00:02:54,570
No, Hyeong-wook!

38
00:02:57,490 --> 00:02:58,491
Hyeong-wook!

39
00:02:59,867 --> 00:03:01,494
Get back in!

40
00:03:01,577 --> 00:03:03,746
Hey! Close the door!

41
00:03:09,085 --> 00:03:13,840
IF WISHES COULD KILL

42
00:03:18,761 --> 00:03:20,430
9:08 a.m.

43
00:03:21,139 --> 00:03:22,515
Yeah, it's a suicide.

44
00:03:25,435 --> 00:03:27,979
This should suffice
without any further statement.

45
00:03:29,939 --> 00:03:30,815
Okay.

46
00:03:31,357 --> 00:03:35,403
Please handle this quickly
for the sake of the other kids.

47
00:03:55,673 --> 00:03:56,549
Ma'am.

48
00:03:56,632 --> 00:03:59,927
I'm going to the gym locker room
to change.

49
00:04:03,681 --> 00:04:06,893
HARD WORK ALWAYS PAYS OFF

50
00:04:13,608 --> 00:04:15,777
Seriously, Choi Hyeong-wook.

51
00:04:16,277 --> 00:04:18,279
Yeah, keep ignoring me like that.

52
00:04:18,988 --> 00:04:20,239
The weather's nice anyway.

53
00:04:20,323 --> 00:04:23,117
I guess I'll just camp out right here
in front of your place!

54
00:04:25,036 --> 00:04:25,995
Hey!

55
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,623
I'm really about to barge in!

56
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,977
I know I bailed on your birthday party,

57
00:04:50,061 --> 00:04:52,021
but do you really have to go this far?

58
00:04:54,065 --> 00:04:56,567
Is that why you're here?
To argue about that?

59
00:05:01,989 --> 00:05:03,074
Just take this.

60
00:05:06,244 --> 00:05:08,413
It's your birthday present, so take it.

61
00:05:08,996 --> 00:05:12,250
I'm giving you one early
since I'm the only one who can't make it.

62
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:13,876
You're the only one?

63
00:05:14,752 --> 00:05:16,629
I already know Geon-woo's not coming.

64
00:05:17,422 --> 00:05:19,632
What? Why wouldn't Geon-woo come?

65
00:05:19,715 --> 00:05:21,592
Geon-woo and Ha-joon will come for sure.

66
00:05:23,052 --> 00:05:25,346
Na-ri will probably be there
to see Geon-woo.

67
00:05:27,014 --> 00:05:29,684
Come on. Just take it already.

68
00:05:30,393 --> 00:05:31,227
Okay?

69
00:05:38,443 --> 00:05:41,028
Here. I'm sorry
I couldn't keep my promise.

70
00:05:41,112 --> 00:05:43,990
I know it doesn't sound like it,
but I came to apologize.

71
00:05:44,615 --> 00:05:45,825
I'll get going now.

72
00:05:54,292 --> 00:05:55,126
Se-ah.

73
00:05:57,712 --> 00:05:58,921
Something…

74
00:06:00,923 --> 00:06:02,842
really strange happened to me today.

75
00:06:04,469 --> 00:06:06,596
I talked to you on the phone today.

76
00:06:07,555 --> 00:06:08,931
Well, technically,

77
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:12,643
I just heard you
talking to the other guys.

78
00:06:16,063 --> 00:06:17,356
But it wasn't you.

79
00:06:19,317 --> 00:06:21,611
I'm sorry I misunderstood, Se-ah.

80
00:06:57,021 --> 00:06:58,439
Se-ah!

81
00:06:59,607 --> 00:07:00,858
Se-ah!

82
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:04,445
Se-ah, are you okay?

83
00:07:05,446 --> 00:07:07,198
Oh God.

84
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:12,495
God, are you okay?

85
00:07:13,079 --> 00:07:14,247
Oh dear.

86
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,998
I'm sorry, Coach.

87
00:07:16,082 --> 00:07:18,417
Why would you be sorry?

88
00:07:18,501 --> 00:07:21,420
Try not to think about anything today.
Just rest at home.

89
00:07:22,004 --> 00:07:24,173
I'll talk to your homeroom teacher.

90
00:07:27,468 --> 00:07:30,846
Training is canceled tomorrow.
Just rest well at home.

91
00:07:30,930 --> 00:07:32,306
Okay?

92
00:07:33,307 --> 00:07:34,141
Okay.

93
00:07:34,225 --> 00:07:36,894
Are you okay going alone?
Do you want me to take you home?

94
00:07:36,978 --> 00:07:37,895
I'm okay.

95
00:07:38,688 --> 00:07:39,814
I can go by myself.

96
00:07:46,779 --> 00:07:49,615
Just rest. Don't worry about training.

97
00:07:52,952 --> 00:07:56,372
Please let Se-ah's training be canceled
this weekend.

98
00:07:56,455 --> 00:07:58,874
It granted a perfect score.
Canceling training should be easy.

99
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:00,042
OCTOBER 24, 2008
KIM GEON-WOO

100
00:08:05,047 --> 00:08:06,048
Coach.

101
00:08:08,301 --> 00:08:11,887
I'm honestly fine now.

102
00:08:13,723 --> 00:08:15,850
Please don't cancel training this weekend.

103
00:08:25,026 --> 00:08:27,361
Hey, Se-ah. Are you okay?

104
00:09:05,149 --> 00:09:05,983
GIRIGO

105
00:09:06,067 --> 00:09:08,569
"Your wish has been granted."

106
00:09:16,535 --> 00:09:17,536
Sorry.

107
00:09:24,585 --> 00:09:25,920
Did the timer come up?

108
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:31,884
It didn't, right?

109
00:09:34,887 --> 00:09:36,931
Did your training really get canceled?

110
00:09:40,476 --> 00:09:41,435
Did your wish

111
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:44,355
come true?

112
00:09:53,781 --> 00:09:56,367
Cancel the training!

113
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:57,993
Cancel! Training!

114
00:09:58,077 --> 00:10:00,204
Cancel the training!

115
00:10:00,287 --> 00:10:02,873
-Cancel the training.
-Please grant Geon-woo's wish.

116
00:10:02,957 --> 00:10:05,376
I'll disconnect it from the network
and reset it.

117
00:10:09,422 --> 00:10:10,381
DELETE ALL

118
00:10:10,464 --> 00:10:11,298
POWERING OFF…

119
00:10:12,258 --> 00:10:15,261
-When did your training get canceled?
-11:26.

120
00:10:16,721 --> 00:10:18,055
That's way too specific.

121
00:10:18,139 --> 00:10:20,266
When the coach said training was canceled,

122
00:10:20,766 --> 00:10:22,226
I checked my phone for the time.

123
00:10:23,394 --> 00:10:24,979
That's when you got the message?

124
00:10:25,062 --> 00:10:26,731
-Yeah.
-Maybe it's hacked.

125
00:10:29,191 --> 00:10:30,109
Possibly.

126
00:10:31,152 --> 00:10:31,986
Look.

127
00:10:32,778 --> 00:10:34,530
I'm telling you, this isn't a hack.

128
00:10:35,698 --> 00:10:37,408
Can a hack kill someone?

129
00:10:37,908 --> 00:10:40,411
Hey, can an app kill someone, then?

130
00:10:41,162 --> 00:10:44,165
A lame app that grants your wishes?

131
00:10:44,749 --> 00:10:47,084
It makes you kill yourself
when the timer hits zero?

132
00:10:47,168 --> 00:10:49,211
Do you seriously think that's real?

133
00:10:49,295 --> 00:10:52,298
The timer appeared
after their wishes were granted.

134
00:10:53,132 --> 00:10:55,009
You all know what happened

135
00:10:56,218 --> 00:10:58,637
when Hyeong-wook's timer hit zero.

136
00:10:58,721 --> 00:10:59,638
Oh, I see.

137
00:11:00,264 --> 00:11:02,558
You saw it,
so we're just supposed to believe you?

138
00:11:02,641 --> 00:11:05,895
The issue isn't that you saw it,
but that only you did.

139
00:11:05,978 --> 00:11:07,646
Are you saying

140
00:11:08,522 --> 00:11:09,857
I'm lying right now?

141
00:11:11,108 --> 00:11:13,527
-Who knows?
-"Who knows?" Fuck! Our friend died today!

142
00:11:13,611 --> 00:11:15,613
That's exactly what I'm trying to say!

143
00:11:15,696 --> 00:11:17,114
-Guys, stop it. Okay?
-Hey!

144
00:11:17,198 --> 00:11:18,657
You're not his only friend!

145
00:11:18,741 --> 00:11:21,410
We were already friends
long before you moved here.

146
00:11:21,494 --> 00:11:23,454
What, is the app possessed by a ghost?

147
00:11:23,537 --> 00:11:26,081
No, maybe you're the one who's possessed.

148
00:11:26,165 --> 00:11:27,958
Just stop it now!

149
00:11:29,877 --> 00:11:31,921
Geon-woo, why do you only cut me off?

150
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:35,883
Did I say anything wrong?
She keeps talking creepy crap!

151
00:11:35,966 --> 00:11:38,135
Na-ri, I didn't mean to. It's just…

152
00:11:41,013 --> 00:11:42,306
I just hate it.

153
00:11:44,558 --> 00:11:48,020
I see my dead mom and dad,
injured so badly I can't recognize them…

154
00:11:50,439 --> 00:11:52,233
in my dreams every night.

155
00:11:53,984 --> 00:11:54,944
Se-ah.

156
00:11:55,027 --> 00:11:55,861
And…

157
00:11:58,030 --> 00:11:59,865
today, right in front of me,

158
00:12:01,617 --> 00:12:03,077
my friend died.

159
00:12:04,703 --> 00:12:07,164
I never want to see
anyone close to me die again.

160
00:12:09,041 --> 00:12:09,875
Not Geon-woo,

161
00:12:11,544 --> 00:12:13,337
not you, not Ha-joon.

162
00:12:13,838 --> 00:12:16,298
Why would we die? That's bullshit.

163
00:12:25,224 --> 00:12:26,058
GIRIGO

164
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:36,986
Whatever it is, it's no ordinary app.

165
00:12:37,069 --> 00:12:38,863
It won't delete, even after a reset.

166
00:12:38,946 --> 00:12:40,072
This won't stop either.

167
00:12:41,991 --> 00:12:43,909
Can't we just break the phone?

168
00:12:43,993 --> 00:12:47,204
We can't. Breaking the phone
won't get rid of the app.

169
00:12:47,288 --> 00:12:49,498
We should take a closer look at this app.

170
00:12:49,582 --> 00:12:52,501
I'll grab my laptop from home.
Then we'll find out.

171
00:12:53,627 --> 00:12:57,172
Then let's get everything we need
and meet at my place.

172
00:13:04,555 --> 00:13:05,639
Na-ri.

173
00:13:07,182 --> 00:13:08,434
You're coming too, right?

174
00:13:10,603 --> 00:13:11,478
Yeah.

175
00:13:35,794 --> 00:13:37,796
About what you said earlier,

176
00:13:39,173 --> 00:13:41,091
that you're having nightmares every night,

177
00:13:41,175 --> 00:13:43,719
I didn't know
you were still struggling like that.

178
00:13:45,012 --> 00:13:45,846
I'm sorry.

179
00:13:50,142 --> 00:13:51,560
When I transferred here,

180
00:13:52,519 --> 00:13:54,396
I was going to quit the track team.

181
00:14:00,527 --> 00:14:02,363
But do you know why I didn't?

182
00:14:04,949 --> 00:14:06,492
Thump.

183
00:14:08,619 --> 00:14:10,496
When I was alone at my aunt's place,

184
00:14:10,996 --> 00:14:12,623
I was so scared and miserable.

185
00:14:13,123 --> 00:14:17,294
But this kid upstairs
kept running around so loudly.

186
00:14:18,921 --> 00:14:20,839
Whenever he saw me at school,

187
00:14:21,340 --> 00:14:24,343
he'd go, "Hey, long jump gold medalist!"

188
00:14:24,426 --> 00:14:27,262
He'd just go off like that.

189
00:14:30,474 --> 00:14:31,308
So

190
00:14:32,726 --> 00:14:34,353
I thought,

191
00:14:35,396 --> 00:14:38,440
"With him around,
I won't be scared even if I'm alone."

192
00:14:41,777 --> 00:14:43,696
Thank you, Geon-woo.

193
00:14:54,873 --> 00:14:56,041
Se-ah.

194
00:14:57,543 --> 00:14:59,211
Do you want me to stay with you?

195
00:15:01,296 --> 00:15:02,589
You don't have to.

196
00:15:03,215 --> 00:15:04,842
We all had a hard time.

197
00:15:05,342 --> 00:15:06,677
Rest up first and come later.

198
00:15:07,553 --> 00:15:08,387
Okay.

199
00:15:35,706 --> 00:15:36,582
SE-AH

200
00:15:38,959 --> 00:15:40,127
Hey, Se-ah.

201
00:15:41,587 --> 00:15:42,463
Hello?

202
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:45,591
Wasn't that fricking hilarious?

203
00:15:46,091 --> 00:15:48,427
"Guys, stop it. Just stop it now."

204
00:15:49,011 --> 00:15:51,972
-That's crazy!
-It's hilarious when that idiot does that.

205
00:15:52,056 --> 00:15:53,098
But Se-ah's alone.

206
00:15:53,182 --> 00:15:55,184
Who the fuck does he think he is?

207
00:15:55,267 --> 00:15:58,145
What do you even see in that idiot
to go out with him?

208
00:15:58,228 --> 00:16:01,106
-You want him?
-Fuck. I'm gonna kill you.

209
00:16:01,190 --> 00:16:02,649
I don't want that loser.

210
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:05,277
How long do you think
that idiot will hold out?

211
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:09,156
I think he'll be joining Choi Hyeong-wook
before sundown.

212
00:16:17,247 --> 00:16:19,208
-Why are you already--
-Quiet.

213
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:21,085
Listen.

214
00:16:26,673 --> 00:16:28,092
Damn it. It hung up.

215
00:16:31,762 --> 00:16:32,930
Maybe my phone's hacked.

216
00:16:33,931 --> 00:16:35,724
They knew everything we said earlier.

217
00:16:36,225 --> 00:16:37,684
-Hacked?
-Yeah.

218
00:16:38,435 --> 00:16:39,269
So…

219
00:16:39,937 --> 00:16:42,272
so the voice sounded just like yours.

220
00:16:42,356 --> 00:16:45,234
But it wasn't you.
There's no way you'd talk like that.

221
00:16:49,196 --> 00:16:50,280
What's wrong?

222
00:16:54,618 --> 00:16:56,453
Hyeong-wook said the same thing.

223
00:16:58,247 --> 00:16:59,832
He said he heard my voice.

224
00:17:05,254 --> 00:17:08,006
I'll move the system apps
and the Girigo files to my laptop

225
00:17:08,090 --> 00:17:09,133
and see what they are.

226
00:17:09,216 --> 00:17:11,802
I can do a factory reset on the phone
to wipe it clean.

227
00:17:14,096 --> 00:17:15,848
What is it? Something's not working?

228
00:17:17,266 --> 00:17:19,393
No. It's weird because it's way too easy.

229
00:17:19,476 --> 00:17:22,354
The code's nothing special.
How is it acting like a system app?

230
00:17:22,437 --> 00:17:23,814
What about the timer?

231
00:17:24,439 --> 00:17:28,152
We can stop and delete
the timer now, right?

232
00:17:28,652 --> 00:17:29,486
Yeah.

233
00:17:37,786 --> 00:17:39,163
It will take a few minutes.

234
00:17:39,246 --> 00:17:40,998
Is it really over now?

235
00:17:41,081 --> 00:17:41,915
Yeah.

236
00:18:03,312 --> 00:18:05,105
Geon-woo, what's wrong?

237
00:18:06,315 --> 00:18:07,316
I don't know.

238
00:18:11,486 --> 00:18:13,447
I think I've got something in my eye.

239
00:18:15,157 --> 00:18:17,159
Geon-woo, stop doing that. Just go rinse--

240
00:18:25,292 --> 00:18:26,293
Geon-woo.

241
00:18:27,169 --> 00:18:28,003
Geon-woo.

242
00:18:37,679 --> 00:18:38,513
Hey…

243
00:18:39,097 --> 00:18:39,932
Hey…

244
00:18:44,144 --> 00:18:45,020
Stay back.

245
00:18:50,484 --> 00:18:52,402
Stay back.

246
00:18:59,826 --> 00:19:01,203
Geon-woo.

247
00:19:10,170 --> 00:19:11,338
Don't do that.

248
00:19:13,048 --> 00:19:13,924
Don't do that.

249
00:19:16,176 --> 00:19:17,135
Don't do that.

250
00:19:19,972 --> 00:19:21,974
Don't do that. Don't…

251
00:19:23,141 --> 00:19:24,268
Geon-woo!

252
00:19:24,351 --> 00:19:25,185
Geon-woo!

253
00:19:30,732 --> 00:19:31,984
Guys, get out.

254
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,321
All of you, out!

255
00:19:37,948 --> 00:19:39,241
I'll get the first aid kit.

256
00:19:39,825 --> 00:19:40,993
Hey, Geon-woo.

257
00:19:43,036 --> 00:19:43,912
Geon-woo!

258
00:19:44,746 --> 00:19:47,958
Se-ah, 119! Se-ah, call 119!

259
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:49,751
Se-ah, now! Se-ah!

260
00:19:53,046 --> 00:19:56,717
Hello, this is Building 323
in Gwangdong Village.

261
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,678
Apartment 608.
Please send an ambulance now!

262
00:19:59,761 --> 00:20:00,637
Geon-woo.

263
00:20:01,346 --> 00:20:02,431
It won't stop bleeding!

264
00:20:03,265 --> 00:20:06,226
Hurry! Send an ambulance!

265
00:20:06,310 --> 00:20:07,311
REBOOTING DEVICE…

266
00:20:07,394 --> 00:20:08,312
Geon-woo.

267
00:20:14,276 --> 00:20:16,069
Don't hang up, and keep talking, okay?

268
00:20:18,697 --> 00:20:19,823
Ma'am!

269
00:20:19,906 --> 00:20:20,907
Ma'am!

270
00:20:28,248 --> 00:20:31,293
Please send the police too…

271
00:20:35,047 --> 00:20:36,465
Goddamn it!

272
00:20:36,548 --> 00:20:37,883
No!

273
00:21:14,211 --> 00:21:16,380
You're the reason
you're all dying, you fucker.

274
00:21:17,089 --> 00:21:18,632
You screwed things up, you nobody.

275
00:21:19,299 --> 00:21:22,344
Now every single one of you will die here.

276
00:21:25,138 --> 00:21:26,014
"I can't breathe."

277
00:21:29,768 --> 00:21:30,894
"Oh, I can't breathe."

278
00:22:11,017 --> 00:22:13,979
SEORIN HOSPITAL

279
00:22:14,688 --> 00:22:15,730
Yoo Se-ah.

280
00:22:16,231 --> 00:22:19,276
You're really not going to tell me
what happened?

281
00:22:19,359 --> 00:22:20,777
How's Geon-woo?

282
00:22:20,861 --> 00:22:22,195
He's in the ICU.

283
00:22:22,279 --> 00:22:26,199
But it's not just the injuries
keeping him from waking up.

284
00:22:26,783 --> 00:22:29,286
If it's not because of me,
then why can't he wake up?

285
00:22:29,369 --> 00:22:32,456
I'm taking special care of Geon-woo,

286
00:22:32,539 --> 00:22:34,166
so he'll get better soon.

287
00:22:37,961 --> 00:22:39,087
Don't worry about him.

288
00:22:40,005 --> 00:22:41,173
Focus on yourself first.

289
00:23:16,416 --> 00:23:18,960
Geon-woo's folks
were looking for you like crazy,

290
00:23:19,044 --> 00:23:21,254
not knowing you kept him
from killing someone.

291
00:23:22,339 --> 00:23:23,507
Do you need anything?

292
00:23:23,590 --> 00:23:25,842
Let me know.
I can bring it from your home.

293
00:23:25,926 --> 00:23:26,927
I'm okay.

294
00:23:28,094 --> 00:23:30,597
My aunt brought
everything I needed earlier.

295
00:23:32,474 --> 00:23:33,558
But what about you?

296
00:23:34,059 --> 00:23:35,810
Isn't your bag at my place?

297
00:23:37,020 --> 00:23:38,813
I can get it later.

298
00:23:38,897 --> 00:23:42,484
The passcode is my birthday,
so just drop by and grab it.

299
00:23:48,823 --> 00:23:52,327
Do you know what I was thinking
when I woke up this morning?

300
00:23:53,828 --> 00:23:55,163
"I'm screwed."

301
00:23:55,247 --> 00:23:56,498
"I'm gonna be late."

302
00:24:01,753 --> 00:24:05,048
That was my biggest worry
just this morning.

303
00:24:05,674 --> 00:24:06,967
Yeah.

304
00:24:08,718 --> 00:24:10,720
How did things end up like this?

305
00:24:21,606 --> 00:24:23,233
KANG HA-YOUNG

306
00:24:34,578 --> 00:24:36,204
-Hello?
-Stop what you're doing!

307
00:24:36,288 --> 00:24:38,582
Don't touch that thing in front of you.

308
00:24:38,665 --> 00:24:40,834
-What?
-You guys messed with it today.

309
00:24:40,917 --> 00:24:42,627
That's why your friend went berserk.

310
00:24:42,711 --> 00:24:44,087
You guys provoked the spirit.

311
00:24:44,671 --> 00:24:46,381
You almost died today.

312
00:24:46,881 --> 00:24:50,719
Whether you believe it or not,
you only survived thanks to that girl.

313
00:24:50,802 --> 00:24:52,554
How do you even know that?

314
00:24:52,637 --> 00:24:54,764
Do you know what you messed with today?

315
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:56,474
What?

316
00:24:56,558 --> 00:24:57,559
Jugu.

317
00:24:58,059 --> 00:24:59,978
It's a conduit that spreads curses.

318
00:25:01,646 --> 00:25:03,690
A smartphone app spreads curses?

319
00:25:03,773 --> 00:25:05,734
Jugu doesn't have a fixed form.

320
00:25:06,234 --> 00:25:09,237
It can be a letter, a drawing,
a photo, or a video.

321
00:25:09,321 --> 00:25:11,823
If it can carry someone's thoughts,

322
00:25:11,906 --> 00:25:14,117
it can be used to spread curses.

323
00:25:16,077 --> 00:25:18,913
Ha-joon, come to me.
I need to see you in person to help you.

324
00:25:18,997 --> 00:25:21,875
You kicked me out last time I went.
Now you want me to go back?

325
00:25:29,299 --> 00:25:31,259
Kang Ha-joon, where is she?

326
00:25:31,343 --> 00:25:32,844
The girl who helped you.

327
00:25:34,846 --> 00:25:35,764
Se-ah?

328
00:25:57,160 --> 00:25:59,913
HA-JOON

329
00:26:23,645 --> 00:26:25,188
Check the heart rhythm.

330
00:26:25,271 --> 00:26:26,523
He's in asystole!

331
00:26:27,023 --> 00:26:28,775
Administering epinephrine!

332
00:26:33,863 --> 00:26:36,366
Come on!

333
00:26:36,950 --> 00:26:38,243
Please, no!

334
00:26:38,910 --> 00:26:41,955
You have to think of Se-ah! Please!

335
00:26:43,873 --> 00:26:45,041
Come on!

336
00:26:52,132 --> 00:26:55,885
GIRIGO
DO YOU WANT TO INSTALL THIS APP?

337
00:26:55,969 --> 00:26:57,512
INSTALLING…

338
00:27:05,186 --> 00:27:06,813
Bangwool, take out your knife.

339
00:27:13,278 --> 00:27:14,404
One.

340
00:27:14,487 --> 00:27:18,658
Write down your name and birthdate
on the paper.

341
00:27:27,667 --> 00:27:28,793
Two.

342
00:27:28,877 --> 00:27:31,296
Hold up the paper
with your saju and name on it,

343
00:27:31,963 --> 00:27:33,548
and open the Girigo app.

344
00:27:35,925 --> 00:27:36,760
Three.

345
00:27:38,136 --> 00:27:39,471
Hit the record button,

346
00:27:40,597 --> 00:27:41,973
and make a wish.

347
00:27:43,266 --> 00:27:44,100
Four.

348
00:27:45,018 --> 00:27:45,852
Make sure…

349
00:27:45,935 --> 00:27:46,770
SEND WISH

350
00:27:46,853 --> 00:27:48,730
…to hit the send button.

351
00:27:48,813 --> 00:27:49,731
SENDING WISH…

352
00:27:53,067 --> 00:27:54,235
Yoo Se-ah!

353
00:27:55,487 --> 00:27:57,322
Did I do it right, Hyeong-wook?

354
00:28:05,455 --> 00:28:06,873
Did you just make a wish?

355
00:28:07,373 --> 00:28:08,249
Are you crazy?

356
00:28:08,333 --> 00:28:10,919
People close to me are dying again,

357
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:13,046
and I can't handle it.

358
00:28:13,129 --> 00:28:15,131
But you're okay with your own death?

359
00:28:19,636 --> 00:28:21,471
You believe in stuff like this?

360
00:28:23,014 --> 00:28:24,641
I thought you hated this stuff.

361
00:28:26,142 --> 00:28:27,644
Se-ah.

362
00:28:27,727 --> 00:28:30,772
There was something else besides us

363
00:28:31,272 --> 00:28:32,649
at school that day.

364
00:28:32,732 --> 00:28:33,942
I said fucking get lost!

365
00:28:37,028 --> 00:28:37,862
Hey…

366
00:28:38,780 --> 00:28:39,614
Hey…

367
00:28:39,697 --> 00:28:42,659
And it was at my place too.

368
00:28:44,619 --> 00:28:47,205
Only those whose wish was granted
can see it.

369
00:28:47,288 --> 00:28:49,249
I need to see what it is. That way…

370
00:28:51,209 --> 00:28:55,171
I can know what they're dealing with
and find the solution.

371
00:29:02,804 --> 00:29:03,638
WISH GRANTED

372
00:29:04,264 --> 00:29:05,431
Five.

373
00:29:06,599 --> 00:29:07,600
The timer

374
00:29:08,643 --> 00:29:10,603
does not stop.

375
00:29:12,063 --> 00:29:14,482
Doctor! He is breathing on his own!

376
00:29:14,566 --> 00:29:17,861
And the last one
Hyeong-wook didn't know about.

377
00:29:20,071 --> 00:29:22,532
When the timer hits zero…

378
00:29:23,908 --> 00:29:26,286
Let Geon-woo return
to exactly the way he used to be.

379
00:29:28,621 --> 00:29:29,455
That's my wish.

380
00:29:33,918 --> 00:29:35,044
…you die.

381
00:30:38,983 --> 00:30:40,693
Eight hours apart.

382
00:30:56,626 --> 00:30:57,961
Did the timer

383
00:30:59,212 --> 00:31:00,546
stop?

384
00:34:55,072 --> 00:34:57,825
Subtitle translation by: Sung In Jang
